  levelNumber: 25
  levelName: Temple of Great Jaguar
  location: "Pet\xE9n, Guatemala"
  levelDescription: "From the Great Plaza, the Jaguar King\u2019s temple rises above
    jungle and time\n\nThe Temple of the Great Jaguar, also known as Temple I, is
    one of the most iconic structures at Tikal, in the Pet\xE9n region of Guatemala.
    Built around 732 AD, it rises about 47 meters (154 feet) above the Great Plaza.\r\n\r\nThis
    pyramid served as the funerary temple of Jasaw Chan K\u2019awiil I, the ruler
    who restored Tikal\u2019s dominance during the Classic Period. Inside, archaeologists
    discovered his tomb filled with jade ornaments, carved bones, and ceremonial
    treasures, underscoring the temple\u2019s role as both a royal mausoleum and
    a sacred monument.\r\n\r\nIts steep steps and towering profile reflect the Maya
    belief in connecting rulers with the divine. Facing the Great Plaza, it formed
    part of Tikal\u2019s ceremonial core, where rituals, processions, and dynastic
    displays took place."
